Happy Mother’s Day to this unbelievable woman! There are so many moments that capture all the different versions of the perfect mom that you are, it’s so hard to choose. It looks different every day, but you are constantly showing up for her. There is absolutely nothing you wouldn’t do - to comfort her in the middle of the night, to give her the most amazing experiences, to make her laugh uncontrollably when nothing else can cheer her up. I see you. When you’re tired, or stressed, or frustrated, and you try and show up for her anyway. I see you, and I’m amazed by you. We love you so much, Happy Mother’s Day @ashleytisdale 💕

Check out Headspace Conversations, the new series on the app now! @headspace 

First short episode with @samanthakai is up today. I was honored to be part of such an incredibly meaningful experience, with the 5 of us strangers (now friends) and an amazing crew of people at Headspace capturing it beautifully. Link in bio ⚡️ #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth

“Anger is a natural, necessary, intelligent emotion we have for a reason. It can also be confusing, destructive and highly addictive.” @tarabrach 

Thanks @headspace for providing this super encouraging atmosphere to shove me out of my comfort zone and say out loud that I have issues with anger. This was such a powerful and transformative experience and I hope others can relate. Check it out on their app today!! 

I especially want to mention that I’ve recently become much more aware of how I’ve had the privilege of more freely expressing my anger in social settings, just by being a white cis-gender man. For many people just “being angry” isn’t so easy. We need to address our issues around anger as a culture, at this point I think that is glaringly obvious.

Check out our recent posts on @frens.he about it as well. Sending you all a little extra love today 🖤

First in a series I’m calling My Favs is my oldest and most reliable guitar: a 2005 Fender Telecaster. This is not custom, or American made - it’s a Mexican Tele I got new for like $250. It just sounds so good, and plays so well, it goes to show you don’t need a fancy expensive guitar to make music. I had it modified with a 4th pickup option and I just love it so much. It’s easily my main go-to, and if I could only keep one instrument, this would be it. If you’ve ever heard any of my music, on an album or in a movie or show, chances are you’ve heard this guitar 🖤 what’s your # 1?
Amen 🙏

Next in My Favorites: the incomparable @sequential_llc Prophet 6. This was the first synthesizer that truly spoke directly to me as an artist. From the first time I messed around with it at @perfect_circuit (and lost like hours which felt like minutes) I knew this one was my board. Hard to explain but it’s just so easy and natural and versatile! I’ve honestly had a harder time getting a *bad* sound out of it than good ones. This is the only keyboard I’ve ever been able to score an entire movie with, and not have it sound repetitive or boring 🖤 Dave Smith you were a true genius, and a personal hero. 

#MyFavoriteInstruments #composer #musician
